a:5:{s:5:"title";s:83:"Membrain adds ConnectWise Orders sync to bring order data into the sales workflow";s:16:"text-format-info";a:3:{s:10:"text-final";s:1184:"<p>Membrain released an integration update that syncs Orders from ConnectWise directly into Membrain.</p>
<h3>What changed</h3>
<p>When enabled, Orders created in ConnectWise are automatically synced to Membrain.</p>
<p>Updates to orders remain synchronized, so sales sees current order information rather than outdated snapshots.</p>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>Order data is often critical for forecasting, revenue understanding, and account health—but it’s typically locked in back-office systems. Syncing ConnectWise Orders into Membrain aims to:</p>
<ul>
<li>reduce manual data entry</li>
<li>lower errors from stale or incomplete information</li>
<li>give sales teams visibility into what’s actually been sold</li>
<li>help leaders base decisions on realized commercial outcomes</li>
</ul>
<h3>What it connects</h3>
<p>The update is positioned to align:</p>
<ul>
<li>what has been ordered,</li>
<li>what’s happening in ongoing sales activity,</li>
<li>and how accounts/opportunities are progressing inside the same workspace.</li>
</ul>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://www.membrain.com/product-updates">https://www.membrain.com/product-updates</a></p>
